  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS). Across base airports: 1 critical, 13 high, 11 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI); plus 11 other bases. 11 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT). Network hotspots: Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN) and 3 others. Primary drivers: very low visibility, RVR limitations and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL) and 9 others.",
